title: For Trade:  NEW PPS 43 (8)/35 ROUND MAGAZINES 202     7.62 x 25 Rounds/ for a  Stainless 1911 45acp
postcontent:
DO NOT SEND ME MESSAGES ASKING HOW MUCH CASH?? OR WHAT DO YOU WANT TO TRADE FOR...IF YOU WANT TO MAKE A OFFER THAN GO AHEAD....IF YOU MESSAGE ME ASKING HOW MUCH OR WHAT YOU LOOKING TO GET I WILL JUST DELETE YOU AND NOT EVEN RESPOND BACK, 


PRICE IS 0.1 CENT because I would rather trade than sell. 

Brand New I.O. Inc Polish PPS-43C pistol is chambered in 7.62x25 Tokarev and makes a fun range plinker. This pistol is manufactured at the famed Radom Plant in Poland from new Polish made parts and components. 

Specifications and Features: 
Caliber: 7.62x25 Tokarev 
Weight: 6.7 lbs empty 
Length: 24" 
Barrel length 9.84" 
Magazine (8) 35 rounds 

The History... 
The PPS-43C (Pistolet-Pulemet Sudaeva, model of 1943 = Sudaev SMG) was born as an answer to the need for a weapon that is more compact and mobile than the PPSh-41, then in use by the Soviet Army. The PPSh-41 was somewhat too long to be used by tank crews and mobile recon groups and paratroopers, so late in 1941, the Red Army issued a request for a new more compact sub machine gun (SMG). The designer Sudaev initially designed his new SMG in 1942, and it was adopted under the designation of PPS-42. The next year he refined the design, and this final model was designated as the PPS-43. This model was manufactured in significant numbers (nearly two million PPS-43 weapons were manufactured between 1943 and 1946). The PPS-43 is sometimes referred to as the best SMG of World War II. After WWII, it was widely exported to pro-Soviet regimes around the world, and widely copied. 

Today... 
I.O. Inc. redesigned this historical firearm to shoot from a closed bolt position. The safety is located at the front of the triggerguard. The receiver and barrel shroud are made from stamped steel. The rear sight is an L-shaped flip type and is marked for 100 and 200 meters, the front sight is a fixed blade type. The barrel is equipped with a simple muzzle brake. This firearm is an ATF approved pistol.

ANY CASH OFFER WELCOME

title: For Sale/Trade:  Magpul 30 round Gen 3 / New in Bags / Dawsonville Gun and Pawn
postcontent:
Please dont flag this. Im just trying to help. Sorry to trick you into opening this but I think its worth the read (BTW, that is what a new Cots msrp is):

Let me first say I shoot in competitions around the country with my guns. I have been buying guns and ammo for over 20 years and have seen this before. I am a Marine and have been buying guns for a long time but this is the worst I have seen it. If you paid more than 1400 for an AR15 unless its an LWRC you paid too much and will see your gun sell for half in six months. I have a reason to have an ar15 but why do you own one...Are you worried that the government will roll down your street and try to take them away. Not going to happen. If you are worried about not ever being able to buy an AR you can buy the lower for 150 to 250 and put it away until you want or need to build one. The lower has the serial # and is essentially the gun.

Gun stores- I wont forget you guys that are taking advantage of this hype and frenzy. Dawsonville Gun and Pawn started out fair but now is whoring out their stuff just like the rest of the gun stores. As an example, they had Magpul Pmags on the shelf and were selling them for 25 plus tax. These cost the dealer less than 8 bucks and msrp is 12. They have an M93 machine pistol that used to sell for $500, then 750 and not they want 999 for it. Sham on you guys. Many of us wont forget! . There are two very fair gun stores in Gainsville I found, you can find them pretty easy and they are right next to each other. 

The other thing that will change is the attitude of the NOT so sales people. These guys used to be nice but now they act like they are doing you a favor. Scott at the Dawsonville Gun and Pawn store is the poster child for dicks that work at gun stores. Avoid this arrogent minimum wage punk at all costs. It will just ruin your fun experience. I promise that when this settles down you will be first to go. This guy needs some ptsd counseling or something.

Now think about all that inventory that is sitting in the hands of gun owners who either dont shoot, purchased on speculation that they could flip the gun or ammo like you flip a house, and the best are those that put 2000 ar rifles on their credit cards. Those bills are now coming in and some cant pay. You dont need an AR 15 to protect yourself. The best home protection is an 870 or Mossbert pump shotgun with a light on it for under $500. Read about home protection on the web.

Its only a matter of time before a ton of inventory hits the street. Dealers will have lots of supply and so will joe consumer. With all that on the market, how much do you think your black rifle will be worth or the 30000 rounds you are sitting on.....Just a thought. Do you remember business school...supply and demand. Dawson Gun and Pawn is already getting calls from people asking if they will buy back the guns they bought.

Dont get caught with that 2000 rifle thats really going to be worth 600 because of the simple law of supply and demand. Youe wont be able to give that rifle away when the factories dump all their orders in the next six months.

What I look forward to is seeing the smug looks of gun dealers being wiped off their faces and their sales staff cut down to one and the owner.

Its going to be a fun ride for AR-15 owners or hoarders of .223 ammo and people paying 30 to $50 for magpul mags that are worth $12.

Good luck

I had big plans for this rifle before finding out that I have a son on the way which changed my priorities real fast. This was purchased as the base for a custom build precision rifle. The Polytechs are often prefered by custom builders over the Springfields for many reasons. I know that these statements infuriate the die hard Springfield guys but the custom build guys happen to side with me on the issue. Please no hate mail attempting to educate me. The rifle shoots great as is but I have already begun the process of building this into a nail driver by purchasing a National Match spring guide by Sadlak and a recoil buffer. postcontent: I have an awesome 19th century baseball that was originally owned and stored by Hall of Famer Amos Rusie who is buried in North Seattle....If you don't know who Amos Rusie is then look him up....He was nicknamed the Hoosier Thunderbolt and is the reason the pitchers mound sits at the distance it is at today....My Dad found this ball in a trunk with many other Amos Rusie stuff back in the 70's at a farm in Renton wa....In the trunk was numerous old cigarette cards, a few balls, a deed and a concealed pistol permit all with Amos Rusies name on them...The other items were sold years ago and this is all that is left....We believe it is one he got while in Japan promoting Baseball with his other teammates, because of the date on the ball and the fact that my Dad was able to track down his Daughter who lived in Seattle and she was able to give a lot of info on the stuff...I had it in an auction about 1 1/2 years ago and it didn't meet my reserve of $2,500...It only got to $1,800 and therefore it didn't sell...It has a date of 1898 on it that is handwritten and numerous signatures that are extremely hard to make out....I was told if I could identify the signatures it would be worth a whole lot more than $2,500...The ball is horsehide and is naturally brown in color....It is an extremely rare piece and I think I am ready to pass it on...If you have something you would like to trade, let me know...I would like it to be in the $1,500-$1,800 range.....But I understand that might not be likely....It could be an extremely lucrative find though... Send me your offers and I will let you know.....One more thing I got a hold of Bobby Rusie recently who is Amos Rusie's Grandson and he was interested in the ball so if I don't get a good offer I might just let it go to him....Thanks

title: For Sale:  Brand New Pepper Spray Keychain, hard case, black in color...**Free Refills for Life
postcontent:
Pepper Spray Keychain, hard case, black in color

If you ever use your "pepper spay" in self-defense, send me a copy of the police report and you'll get free re-fills.
=================
About Pepper Spray:

This spray has an Ultra-Violet Light Identifying Dye (which helps to ID these Ass-holes) includes both a clip (to easily attach it to your clothes while walking) and a key ring.

PEPPER SPRAY FACTS: Pepper spray enables you to defend yourself while keeping a safe distance from an attacker. Pepper sprays induce an almost immediate burning sensation of the skin and a burning, tearing, and swelling of the eyes. If spray is inhaled, the respiratory tract becomes inflamed resulting in a swelling of the mucous membranes lining the breathing passages and temporarily restricting breathing to short, shallow breaths. A one second burst to the face will cause temporary blindness, choking, coughing, and nausea-disabling your attacker giving you time to escape.

The active ingredient in this spray is Oleoresin Capsicum (O.C.), commonly referred to as red pepper. It is a natural, oily, resin-like substance derived from hot peppers, the same peppers used to make spicy foods hot.

When considering which pepper spray is most effective, one must consider the percentage of pepper being used and the heat rating of that pepper (measured in Scoville Heat Units or S.H.U.). A good pepper sprays has a rating of 2 million S.H.U. or higher...

**Don't be fooled by the claims "Hottest allowed by law" and "Hottest in the industry" that are made by some on the web. This gives people a false sense of security.**

FYI...Capsaicinoid Concentration is the determination of active components in Oleoresin Capsicum. Capsaicinoids
are the group of compounds that cause the burning sensation. There are the three main compounds that make
up about 95% of the Capsaicinoids: Capsaicin, Dihydrocapsaicin, and Nordihydrocapsaicin. The Capsaicinoid
Concentration is the amount of these compounds in a certain solution. Therefore, by measuring the amount
of capsaicinoids, an accurate level of pungency can be determined for the solution. This is the unit of
measurement that is the most consistent and best representation throughout all grades of Oleoresin Capsicum.
In essence, it is the equaling factor between SHUâ€™s and % OC.

While the strength of the selected peppers may vary from year to year or between seasons, the measurement
of capsaicinoids is consistent in determining that hotness. A 0.2% Capsaicinoid Concentration will yield the
same amount of hotness, regardless of the batch of peppers or their location of cultivation. For this reason, it
is the only accurate method of determining the pungency of peppers. The current detection method for this
analysis is by High-Performance Liquid Chromatography, HPLC.4 Therefore, by establishing quality control
monitoring the capsaicinoid concentration, a consistent strength or pungency can be easily obtained and
verified by this analysis.

**Federal law does not allow carrying any type of pepper spray on airplanes or in the security areas of an airport. They are also prohibited on aircraft because the drop in air pressure can cause the pepper spray canisters to explode. For the same reason, pepper spray cannot be shipped by air. **If you're flying, I'll tell/show you how to make your spray "airplane safe". Just e-mail me.

Always remember that you assume all risk and liability for owning and using pepper spray. Even if you use it correctly, there is no guarantee that it will always be effective at hindering an attack, and there is always the possibility that it may be used against you instead.

**Consult the laws of your state and/or local agency. Understand and Obey them before owning pepper spray.**

-------------------

**Revised Code of Washington 9.91.160**

Personal protection spray devices.

(1) It is unlawful for a person under eighteen years old, unless the person is at least fourteen years old and has the permission of a parent or guardian to do so, to purchase or possess a personal protection spray device. A violation of this subsection is a misdemeanor.

(2) No town, city, county, special purpose district, quasi-municipal corporation or other unit of government may prohibit a person eighteen years old or older, or a person fourteen years old or older who has the permission of a parent or guardian to do so, from purchasing or possessing a personal protection spray device or from using such a device in a manner consistent with the authorized use of force under RCW 9A.16.020. No town, city, county, special purpose district, quasi-municipal corporation, or other unit of government may prohibit a person eighteen years old or older from delivering a personal protection spray device to a person authorized to possess such a device.

(3) For purposes of this section:

(a) "Personal protection spray device" means a commercially available dispensing device designed and intended for use in self-defense and containing a non-lethal sternutator or lacrimator agent, including but not limited to:

(i) Tear gas, the active ingredient of which is either chloracetophenone (CN) or O-chlorobenzylidene malonotrile (CS); or

(ii) Other agent commonly known as mace, pepper mace, or pepper gas.

(b) "Delivering" means actual, constructive, or attempted transferring from one person to another.

(4) Nothing in this section authorizes the delivery, purchase, possession, or use of any device or chemical agent that is otherwise prohibited by state law.
